<item>
            <title>[LU-1609] Remove dynlock patch from ldiskfs</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1609</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;we still have embedded dynlock in all ldiskfs_inodes which takes extra 24 bytes (actually 28 bytes because it&apos;s not 8 bytes aligned), however, the only use-case now is for IAM container, so we should:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;remove dynlock patch and move it into osd-ldiskfs&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;add a new field for iam_container::ic_lock&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s too late to have this for 2.3, but we should do this at least for the next release.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
